50 commission based on the requirements established by the
51 commission;
52 (6) For payment of Missouri National Guard and
53 Missouri veterans commission expenses associated with
54 providing medals, medallions and certificates in recognition
55 of service in the Armed Forces of the United States during
56 World War II, the Korean Conflict, and the Vietnam War under
57 sections 42.170 to 42.226. Any funds remaining from the
58 medals, medallions and certificates shall not be transferred
59 to any other fund and shall only be utilized for the
60 awarding of future medals, medallions, and certificates in
61 recognition of service in the Armed Forces;
62 (7) Fund transfers totaling ten million dollars to any
63 municipality with a population greater than three hundred
64 fifty thousand inhabitants and located in part in a county
65 with a population greater than six hundred thousand
66 inhabitants and with a charter form of government, for the
67 sole purpose of the construction, restoration, renovation
68 and maintenance of a memorial or museum or both dedicated to
69 World War I; [and]
